    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div>
          <h2>Human Nature Reality ‚Äî short meaning</h2>
          <p class="muted">Human has its nature. Nature can create, preserve and destroy ‚Äî a rule that spans from smallest life to the cosmos. Human nature builds realities: inventions, social systems, philosophies, and tools that can heal or harm. This site explores those three words ‚Äî <strong>Human</strong>, <strong>Nature</strong>, <strong>Reality</strong> ‚Äî and offers paths to reflect, learn and act.</p>

          <div class="section card" id="human">
            <h3>Human ‚Äî <span class="mini muted">Guru ‚Ä¢ Antiguru ‚Ä¢ Nonguru</span></h3>
            <div class="three-cols">
              <div class="pill">
                <strong>Guru</strong>
                <div class="small">A path toward truth, peace, or happiness followed across ages. Traditions, teachers, methods that point toward meaning.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="pill">
                <strong>Antiguru</strong>
                <div class="small">When the supposed path misleads, mismanages, or creates opposites of the promised ideals. False promises and harmful systems.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="pill">
                <strong>Nonguru</strong>
                <div class="small">No prescribed path ‚Äî only silence and natural intelligence. A perspective that trusts nature's spontaneous intelligence rather than promised maps.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="section card" id="nature">
            <h3>Nature</h3>
            <p class="muted">Nature holds intelligence in many forms. On this site we juxtapose:</p>
            <div class="three-cols" style="margin-top:8px">
              <div class="pill">
                <strong>Natural Intelligence</strong>
                <div class="small">Biological, ecological, and emergent intelligence found in living systems and natural processes.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="pill">
                <strong>Artificial Intelligence</strong>
                <div class="small">Human-made systems that simulate or extend intelligence. We explore how AI intersects with human nature and ethical choices.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="pill">
                <strong>Harmony</strong>
                <div class="small">How natural and artificial intelligence might coexist or clash ‚Äî and how to steer that relation responsibly.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="section card" id="reality">
            <h3>Reality</h3>
            <p class="muted">Reality is our created world ‚Äî inventions, institutions, laws, preservation and destruction performed in the name of progress, peace or happiness. Here we document, critique, and celebrate examples from technology, society and culture.</p>
            <ul class="small muted">
              <li>Inventions & tools (benefits & risks)</li>
              <li>Social structures & economics (money, power, welfare)</li>
              <li>Preservation & destruction (ecology, weapons, repair)</li>
            </ul>
